items.name: Akakura
items.description:
采用p站画师赤倉（https://www.pixiv.net/users/882569 ） 的部分作品训练而成，主要是2023年新出作品，训练集由@ Eisthol帮忙整理，并在他的指导下训练完成。

和Plain style（https://civitai.com/models/108834/plain-style ） 的训练集相同。

因为Eisthol的风格是以更少的图片出更好的模型，所以整个训练集仅有24张作品。

同时也是我Akakura系列的第7代（因为之前的结果一直不理想）

画师特有的失真滤镜没有学会，不过整体而言，效果还是不错的。

但是有一个明显的缺点，因为训练集的原因，不能生成很好的手部

模型的建议权重为：0.8

--小剧场--

我：我可以发C站吗，我自己炼这个

Eisthol：发呗，反正我已经发c了（

我：感觉很像啊（指数据集一样）

Eisthol：hash值不一样的，有人骂了我出来帮你

这个是我的第一个画风模型，感谢E大对我的无限耐心指导！

The model, named Plain Style - v1.0 | Stable Diffusion LoRA | Civitai, was trained using some of the works by the P-site artist Akakura (https://www.pixiv.net/users/882569), ↗,) mainly focusing on their new works released in 2023. The training set was compiled with the help of @Eistho, who also provided guidance throughout the training process.

The training set is the same as that of Plain Style (https://civitai.com/models/108834/plain-style). ↗.)

As Eisthol's style produces better models with fewer images, the entire training set consisted of only 24 works. This is also the 7th generation of my Akakura series, as the previous results were not satisfactory.

The unique distortion filter of the artist was not learned by the model, but overall, the results are still good.

However, there is a noticeable drawback: due to the limitations of the training set, the model cannot generate good-looking hands.

The suggested weight of the model is 0.8.

-- Small Theater --

Me: Can I post this on C-site and train it myself?

Eisthol: Sure, I've already posted it on civitai.

Me: It feels very similar (referring to the same dataset).

Eisthol: The hash values are different. Someone scolded me for coming out to help you.

This is my first style model, and I am grateful for Eisthol's infinite patience and guidance!

items.description:
Intro

In this model has all the character, can achieve higher pitch. Gotou Futari is the cutest voice and able produce higher output quality even just 10 files at ~10 seconds each, Male Voice to Gotou Futari need to Crepe +6 pitch (0.5 octave) transpose (adjust depending how deep source is). Sample AI song are down below.

Dataset

Source dataset is from streaming services, model quality hard to achieve due to lossy codec (MP3/AAC/Opus), perhaps waiting BD Remux/FLAC release and rip from there, so processing, clean-up will be much better than ripping from the web

Infer

It has usual so-vits-svc-fork and rvc, I not sure which one is good, but rvc train much quicker but still artifact at breathing/whisper/low loudness

Post Processing

EffectPresets.xml included inside v2.1 zip file, read the readme.txt file please

items.name: Booker DeWitt | BioShock Infinite
items.description:
Character Lora of Booker DeWitt from BioShock Infinite

"City at the bottom of the ocean? Ridiculous." -Booker DeWitt

Father of the year -soul3142


This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International License.

If you want to, you can support me on Patreon or Buy me Coffee.

Main Trigger Word - bookerBS_soul3142 , check examples for other ones.

RECOMMENDATIONS :-

  1. Highres Fix - must, if you are getting blurry and ugly images

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.6 - 0.8

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Denoising - Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

  5. For better face's - you can use ADetailer

I use 0.7 weight, 25 steps, Euler a, Clip skip 2 in nearly all my examples with almost same, simple +ve/-ve prompts regardless of checkpoint for my own consistency purposes.

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not (usually character's with single costume) so keep these things in mind.

This is an unofficial fanmade LoRA, not intended for any commercial purpose and use. All characters and IP rights are owned by their respective creators and owners. I do not own rights to any of these characters.

items.name: Luisa Neubauer (JG)
items.description:
A request of @lemke.

Luisa Neubauer is a German climate activist and politician.

140-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (n3ub4u3r:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: A Trip to the Moon - lavish 1900s scifi
items.description:
This model was trained on hand-coloured prints of the 1902 motion picture A Trip to the Moon (Le voyage dans la lune). Written by, directed by and starring Georges Méliès, the film took audiences on a fantastic journey to the Moon by means of never-before-seen practical effects. The film's ornate visual style is rooted in the French tradition of féerie or fairy plays, which featured beautiful costumes and lavish mechanised scenery.

This model recreates the ethereal colour tones and intricate design elements of the original film. Given the source material, it is well suited to steampunk or retro scifi themes. Bon voyage!

items.name: Citroën DS (70s)
items.description:
You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

You can also subscribe to my Patreon and get exclusive models.

The Citroën DS is a front mid-engined, front-wheel drive executive car manufactured and marketed by Citroën from 1955 to 1975, in fastback/sedan, wagon/estate, and convertible body configurations, across three series of one generation.

The DS was known for its aerodynamic, futuristic body design; unorthodox, quirky, and innovative technology, and it set new standards in ride quality, handling, and braking, thanks to both being the first mass production car equipped with hydropneumatic suspension, as well as disc brakes. The 1967 series 3 also introduced directional headlights to a mass-produced car.

Italian sculptor and industrial designer Flaminio Bertoni and the French aeronautical engineer André Lefèbvre styled and engineered the car, and Paul Magès developed the hydropneumatic self-levelling suspension. Robert Opron designed the 1967 Series 3 facelift. Citroën built 1,455,746 examples in six countries, of which 1,330,755 manufactured at Citroën's main Paris Quai de Javel (now Quai André-Citroën) production plant.

In combination with Citroën's proven front-wheel drive, the DS was used competitively in rally racing during almost its entire 20‑year production run, and achieved multiple major victories, as early as 1959, and as late as 1974. It placed third in the 1999 Car of the Century poll recognizing the world's most influential auto designs and was named the most beautiful car of all time by Classic & Sports Car magazine.
